§ DEPENDENCY POLICY
  stage0 : Rust-ecosystem crates allowed (throwaway)
  stage1+ : zero-runtime-deps (CSSLv3 self-sufficient)
  banned ∀ stages : LLVM, clang, gcc-as-lib, closed-source-blobs
  allowed external IRs/libs : MLIR (Apache-2-LLVM-exception),
    SPIR-V-spec, Vulkan-spec, Z3/CVC5 (MIT/BSD)

§ REPRODUCIBILITY COMMITMENT
  W! never accept binary-only stage
  stage0-Rust source = auditable
  stage1-CSSLv3 source = auditable
  stage3 C99-tarball = rebuildable anywhere
  CI : build-from-scratch C99 → stage3-C → stage1 → stage1' reproducible
  audit-signed by Apocky-key + CI-key chain

§ SUCCESS GATES
  stage0 :
    examples/hello-triangle.cssl compiles + runs on Arc-A770 (Vulkan)
    examples/hello-triangle.cssl compiles + runs on Arc-A770 (Level-Zero)
    examples/sdf-shader.cssl : @differentiable normals bit-exact vs analytic
    audio_cb-with-{NoAlloc} : alloc-in-callback = compile-error
    layout-mismatch CPU↔GPU = compile-error
    {Telemetry<Counters>} captures power-samples on Arc (R18)
    differential-test Vulkan-vs-L0 same-SPIR-V bit-exact
  stage1 :
    self-compile fixed-point ≤ 2 min elapsed
    own-x86-64-backend matches Cranelift perf ±10%
    all F1..F6 + R1..R18 present
  stage2 :
    LoA running on CSSLv3 • 60fps Arc A770 vertical-slice-floor
    Odin-v10 archived
  stage3 :
    CI reproducible-from-C99 green
    signed attestation published per-version

§ RISK → MITIGATION
  no time-cap-trap : N/A (Phase-C pacing, not calendar-driven)
  Cranelift-perf-gap : stage1 own-backend closes-it
  SPIR-V-validation-bugs : spirv-val + differential-testing (§§ 23) mandatory
  MLIR-ABI-drift : pinned to LLVM release + vendored MLIR-sys bindings
  Z3/CVC5-solver-drift : pinned versions + CI matrix
  Level-Zero-API-evolution : pinned L0-spec version + runtime-feature-check
  driver-bugs (Arc BDA/bindless corner-cases) : differential-test catches
  self-hosting-regression : stage0 maintained through stage1+stage2 transition

∎ BOOTSTRAP
